table; for startups or thin teams, use a founder, CTO, VP Engineering, Head of Engineering, hiring manager, or technical lead.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- Prefer university, campus, emerging talent, early-career, intern, new grad, SWE, AI, ML, or technical recruiting titles.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- In bolster mode, technical members who are publicly hiring for their team are valid, especially for internship, new-grad, SWE, AI, ML, data, infrastructure, or product engineering roles.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- US-based or clearly US-hiring people are preferred.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- Never add more than 10 contacts to a company. If it already has 10 or more, skip it unless correcting stale data.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- Use only public professional information. Do not scrape aggressively.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nRecruiter object schema:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n```json\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n{\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"name\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"title\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"linkedin_url\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\